Feature: the canonical lead CLAUDE.md primer directs the router to proactively initiate a product-discovery conversation when it detects an effectively-empty repo, instead of declaring idle

  lead-vglj (P2) — product authority 2026-06-29 (verbatim): "for the lead to
  detect when the repo is effectively empty and start a product discovery
  conversation with the user to start determining the shape of the new system."

  This scenario pins the PROACTIVE-INITIATION trigger: on detecting the
  effectively-empty / no-product-defined state (the two-signal test defined by
  the sibling detection scenario) at session start or during the idle-detection
  checklist, the router must OPEN a product-discovery conversation with the
  product authority rather than declaring idle and waiting for a prompt. This is
  the empty-repo TRIGGER that fires the existing product-authority discovery gate.

  Single behavior: the trigger fires discovery instead of idle, at the
  router / main-agent level. The re-fire cadence and the brainstorm-then-branch
  opener shape are pinned by sibling scenarios in this family, not here.

  Design alignment (reference, do not contradict): the existing product-authority
  discovery gate already establishes that the discovery DIALOGUE happens at the
  main-agent / router level because discovery subagents are non-interactive and
  cannot conduct it. This scenario adds the trigger that fires that dialogue
  proactively; it must NOT pin a non-interactive subagent doing the talking.

  AUTHORING ONLY — no BC dispatch. @bc tag is the Architect's to apply at
  assignment time; @lead_integration:templates below is provisional placement
  matching sibling primer-furniture scenarios.

